      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Mercy-USA excels in technical humanitarian interventions that require long-term presence. Their <cite id=\"6\">modular home construction project</cite> in Syria provided immediate dignity and shelter to 950 families, while their <cite id=\"13\">seasonal food aid reached 10 countries</cite> in 2023. This operational depth is supported by a <cite id=\"14\">Platinum Seal of Transparency</cite> from Candid and <cite id=\"15\">perfect 100/100 scores</cite> in both Culture and Leadership metrics from Charity Navigator."
      ],
      "summary": "Founded in <cite id=\"1\">1988</cite>, Mercy-USA for Aid and Development has established itself as a major humanitarian actor, focusing on <cite id=\"2\">nutrition support and health services</cite> for vulnerable populations. The organization reported <cite id=\"3\">$54,067,823 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 fiscal year, maintaining a lean operational model with a <cite id=\"4\">fundraising efficiency of $0.03 per $1 raised</cite>. Their work is characterized by direct service delivery in high-need regions, including <cite id=\"5\">Somalia, Syria, and Gaza</cite>. In 2022 alone, the charity successfully <cite id=\"6\">built 950 modular homes</cite> and maintained a <cite id=\"7\">80% TB cure rate</cite> through its specialized health centers. Beyond medical care, Mercy-USA is a significant provider of sustainable infrastructure, having <cite id=\"8\">dug or repaired 800 wells</cite> to provide safe water access. The organization is <cite id=\"9\">zakat-eligible</cite>, with policies ensuring funds reach the <cite id=\"10\">fuqara (poor), masakin (needy), and ibn al-sabil (wayfarers)</cite>. While its <cite id=\"11\">overall Charity Navigator score is 92.33/100</cite>, the organization operates with <cite id=\"12\">0.8 months of working capital</cite>, indicating a high reliance on consistent donor support to maintain its extensive international programs.",
